<section class="brand--ministry-of-defence brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="what-we-do">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">What the Armed Forces' Pay Review Body does</h2>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
    
          <p></p>
<div class="govspeak">
<p>The Armed Forces’ Pay Review Body (AFPRB) provides independent advice to the Prime Minister and the Secretary of State for Defence on the pay and charges for members of the Naval, Military and Air Forces of the Crown.</p>

<p><abbr title="Armed Forces' Pay Review Body">AFPRB</abbr> is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class="brand__color" href="/government/organisations/ministry-of-defence">Ministry of Defence</a>.</p>
</div>

          <p>
            <a href="/government/organisations/armed-forces-pay-review-body/about" class="brand__color">
              Read more about what we do
            </a>
          </p>

</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



